## Implementation Notes

Emit values until notifier fires, then complete.

### Approach
```rust
pub trait TakeUntilExt<T>: Watchable<T> {
    fn take_until<U, M>(&self, notifier: &Cell<U, M>) -> Cell<T, CellImmutable>
```

### Key Implementation Details
- Use `Arc<AtomicBool>` to track "stopped" state
- Watch source: if !stopped, emit value
- Watch notifier: on first emission, set stopped=true
- Optionally unsubscribe from source (needs disposal rx3-7m0)

### Implementation
```rust
let stopped = Arc::new(AtomicBool::new(false));

// Watch notifier
notifier.watch(move |_| {
    stopped.store(true, Ordering::SeqCst);
    // TODO: unsubscribe from source, signal completion
});

// Watch source
self.watch(move |value| {
    if !stopped.load(Ordering::SeqCst) {
        derived.notify(value.clone());
    }
});
```

### Files to Create/Modify
- Create: `src/traits/take_until.rs`
- Modify: `src/traits/mod.rs`

### Test Cases
- take_until with delayed notifier
- Verify emissions stop after notifier fires
- Verify no emissions if notifier fires immediately

## Implementation Notes

Error if no emission within duration.

### Approach
```rust
pub trait TimeoutExt<T>: Watchable<T> {
    fn timeout(&self, duration: Duration) -> Cell<Result<T, TimeoutError>, CellImmutable>
}
```

### Key Implementation Details
- Similar to debounce pattern with generation counter
- On each emission, reset timer
- Spawn thread: sleep(duration), check if emission occurred
- If no emission, emit error (or complete with error)

### Implementation Pattern
```rust
let generation = Arc::new(AtomicU64::new(0));
self.watch(move |value| {
    generation.fetch_add(1, Ordering::SeqCst);
    // ... emit value
});
// Timeout thread checks if generation changed
```

### Output Type Options
- `Cell<Result<T, TimeoutError>>` - explicit error
- `Cell<Option<T>>` with None on timeout
- Signal error through error channel (needs rx3-cgz)

### Files to Create/Modify
- Create: `src/traits/timeout.rs`
- Create: `src/error.rs` for TimeoutError type
- Modify: `src/traits/mod.rs`

