## Location
`rx3-lib/src/traits/operators/switch_map.rs:74-84, 112-122, 129-136`

## Problem
Same TOCTOU pattern as merge. Inner completion and outer completion check each other's flags separately:

```rust
// Inner completion (line 76-82)
if cg.load(...) == 0 {
    ic.store(true, ...);
    if oc.load(...) { complete() }
}

// Outer completion (line 130-134)
outer_complete.store(true, ...);
if inner_complete.load(...) { complete() }
```

If inner and outer complete simultaneously, both may miss.

## Fix
Same as merge - use combined atomic state with compare-exchange or fetch_or.

Thread safety issues in timing operators:

**debounce.rs:18-30** - Generation counter race:
```rust
let my_gen = generation.fetch_add(1, Ordering::SeqCst) + 1;
thread::spawn(move || {
    thread::sleep(duration);
    if generation.load(Ordering::SeqCst) == my_gen {  // RACE
        c.notify(value);
    }
});
```
Between sleep completing and load, another update could occur.

**throttle.rs:18-27** - Thread spawns after notify:
```rust
if can_emit.swap(false, Ordering::SeqCst) {
    c.notify(value.clone());  // Notify happens BEFORE...
    thread::spawn(move || {   // ...thread is spawned
        thread::sleep(duration);
        can_emit.store(true, Ordering::SeqCst);
    });
}
```
Updates can pile up between notify and thread spawn.

Need proper synchronization or use tokio timers.

CRITICAL: interval() and from_iter_with_delay() spawn threads with infinite loops that can never be stopped.

interval.rs:
```rust
thread::spawn(move || {
    loop {  // NEVER EXITS
        thread::sleep(duration);
        c.notify(count);
    }
});
```

Issues:
- Thread runs forever even if Cell is dropped
- No cancellation token or stop signal
- Resource exhaustion with many intervals

Need:
1. Cancellation token (Arc<AtomicBool>) checked in loop
2. Return handle that can stop the thread
3. Auto-stop when Cell has no subscribers or is dropped

State machine operator for defining valid transitions and transition handlers:

```rust
enum State { Idle, Loading, Ready, Error }

source.state_machine(|sm| {
    sm.on(Idle, Loading, |_| println!("started loading"));
    sm.on(Loading, Ready, |_| println!("load complete"));
    sm.on(Loading, Error, |e| println!("load failed"));
    sm.on_any(Error, |_| println!("entering error state"));
    // Invalid transitions could be ignored or error
})
```

Features:
