- Could return Cell<State> that only updates on valid transitions

cell.rs:147-152 - notify() iterates subscribers while callbacks execute:

```rust
pub fn notify(&self, value: T) {
    self.inner.value.store(Arc::new(value.clone()));
    self.inner.subscribers.iter().for_each(|subscriber| {
        (subscriber.callback)(&value);  // Callback runs here
    });
}
```

Issues:
1. New subscriber added during iteration gets wrong initial value
2. Subscriber removed mid-iteration (DashMap handles but order undefined)
3. If callback modifies cell or subscribers, undefined behavior
4. DashMap iterator holds read lock for duration of ALL callbacks

If callback is slow, all other operations on subscribers are blocked.

